### Python Cache & Bytecode ###
# Avoid tracking compiled bytecode (.pyc) which Python generates automatically to run faster
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class

### Virtual Environments ###
# Keeps your heavy local dependency sandboxes out of the repository
.venv/
venv/
env/
ENV/

### Environment Variables & Secrets ###
# CRITICAL: Never track files containing API keys, database credentials, or private configuration tokens
.env
.env.*
*.env

### IDE & Text Editor Artifacts ###
# Keeps local editor settings from fighting with someone else's screen setup
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo

### Testing, Coverage, & Code Analysis ###
# Keeps temporary debugging reports out of the clean codebase
.pytest_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

### Distribution & Packaging (If packaging your app later) ###
# Temporary directories created when bundling Python code into shareable modules
build/
dist/
*.egg-info/
